Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2015=20patch=200071=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20dirty-rect=20re-enable=20via=20Lever=20B=20per-blit=20destin?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ation=20tracking?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Re-author of the wave 9 dirty-rect optimization (patch 0052, commit
96d8e04) that was reverted in wave 10 (commit 8a9551e) due to
sprite-trail / menu-fragment artifacts on real Cirrus. See
docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §4 for the spec.

Wave 9's failure mode was structural: it SKIPPED drawcalls based on
per-call FNV-1a fingerprints (op_type+surface+rects+alpha+color), with
the assumption that "matching fingerprint = backbuffer pixels already
correct from last frame." But skipping a blit doesn't restore the
surrounding pixels that prior writes mutated — when the index-aligned
compare diverged mid-frame, the in-flight backbuffer state was already
inconsistent with the assumed last-frame contents at every prior
fingerprint-match index.

Wave 15 leverages the wave 12.1-12.5 hand-rolled blit primitives
(patches 0054-0060) which write directly through
_cached_window_surface->pixels via _blit_rgb565 / _blit_rgb565_mirrored
/ _blit_rgb565_alpha / _blit_rgb565_color_mod_{black,general}, plus the
hand-rolled clearScreen / fillRect / drawRect / drawLine paths. Every
such primitive knows its destination rect by construction, so wave 15
records dirty rects accurately without the brittle fingerprint compare.

Implementation:

  Pass 1 (drawcall accumulation): each blit primitive calls
  _record_dirty_rect(dst.x, dst.y, dst.w, dst.h) post-blit. The helper
  clips to the 320×240 viewport, drops empties, and applies cheap
  in-place coalescing (drop-if-contained, union-on-overlap, collapse-
  to-bounding-box at DIRTY_RECTS_MAX=16).

  Pass 2 (Renderer::flip): sums dirty pixel area; if total exceeds
  DIRTY_THRESHOLD_PIXELS (38400 = 50% of 320×240), falls back to
  SDL_RenderPresent. Otherwise calls SDL_FlushRenderer (drain any
  slow-path queued commands) then SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects on the
  rect list. Conservative fall-throughs to full flush:
    - first DIRTY_FIRST_N_FRAMES=3 frames after init / flushAll
    - _force_full_refresh set externally
    - dirty list empty (treat as "either nothing changed or some path
      bypassed _record_dirty_rect; full flush is cheap insurance")
    - _dirty_rect_enabled false (env-var kill switch)

  Wired into every primitive that already had wave-9 plumbing:
    drawSurface, drawSurfaceMirrored, drawSurfaceColorMod (the latter
    covers all Font.cpp glyph runs after wave 12.5), blitPatternAcross,
    drawLine, drawRect, fillRect, tintScreen, drawPixel (via fillRect),
    clearScreen, drawSpotLight.

Removed (no longer needed): the FNV-1a hash machinery (FNV_1A_OFFSET,
FNV_1A_PRIME, _fnv_step, DrawcallOp enum, _hash_drawcall), the
_check_skip_drawcall hot-path skip helper, the
_current_frame_calls / _last_frame_calls fingerprint vectors, the
_first_diverging_call cliff index, the _current_clear_color /
_last_clear_color color-change tracking, the FORCE_FULL_REFRESH_EVERY
periodic-paranoia constant, and the _dr_skipped_calls_block /
_dr_first_diverge_* skip diagnostics.

Env-gate semantics flipped (default was OFF since wave 10):
  - Default ON
  - SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRTY_RECTS=0 — force-disable (kill switch)
  - Anything else (unset, =1, any other value) — enabled
The "1"-only strict match used elsewhere is inverted here because the
default is ON; we want a clear escape hatch and don't want a stray
non-empty value to accidentally disable a perf win.

Diagnostic block (per-100-flip cadence, existing dirty-rect block
LOG_INFO line rewired):
  total_calls         — drawcalls executed in the block
  dirty_rects_avg     — mean rect-list length per flip
  dirty_pct_x10       — mean dirty-pixel area as permille of screen
  forced_full         — flips with _force_full_refresh set
  first_n_force       — flips inside the first-N-frames guard
  threshold_exceeded  — flips that fell back due to >50% dirty area
  dirty_path_taken    — flips that used SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects
  full_flush_taken    — flips that used SDL_RenderPresent

Predicted impact (per plan §4): 10-30 ms / flip win on static scenes
(menu idle, dialog text idle); cmod-heavy menus may not benefit much
because whole-screen color-mod sweeps tend to mark the entire
viewport dirty, tripping the threshold. Net: title scene
inter_flip_ms expected to drop from ~98 ms to ~70-85 ms; gameplay
scenes should improve more (most pixels static frame-to-frame). Real-
HW iter required to confirm — DOSBox-X is correctness-only per
docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md.
